e, depicting a horse standing on four legs with calves at the ends of the limbs; the mouth is open, and a rope is shown on the back, interpreted as indicating a harness for pulling a wagon. Bronze. 4th–3rd centuries BC. Height 12.1 cm; length 13.8 cm.'),('0- _10_p063_7c650d5d','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','South Arabian antiquity','1st century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',63,'Bronze human statue in standing position, with the lower extremities scattered and the upper left extremities broken. The chest has a hollow cavity in the form of an inverted triangle, and the waist is encircled by a belt. Dated to the 1st century BC–1st century AD.'),('0- _10_p064_849e91cc','sculpture','head','stone','human','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',64,'Head-shaped tombstone, stone: carved in Albister stone, depicting a human head in relief with hair falling from below the ears to the back of the head, triangular eyes, a straight nose, and a small closed mouth.'),('0- _10_p065_20d411b4','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',65,'Human statue, marble stone, with clear features, standing on a base; both hands are extended forward and broken, and the lower limbs are set on a cubic-shaped base. The current condition of the piece is very good.'),('0- _10_p066_24a6970b','stone monument','tombstone','stone','human','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',66,'Tombstone, stone: carved funerary marker with a human head in relief, from Albister stone. The face is shown with lightly incised eyes, ears on both sides of the head, a straight nose, and a beard indicated below the mouth.'),('0- _10_p067_ac96fcd1','sculpture','statue','bronze','camel','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',67,'Statue, bronze. Camel statue with a passenger on its back, showing clear features; the rider is depicted holding a stone. The camel has a straight neck and a forward-facing head, rendered in motion. Dated to the 1st century BC.'),('0- _10_p068_ba9aadb6','currency','coin','unknown','human;owl','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',68,'Coin, metal, 4.85 g. Ancient Yemeni coin dated 354–340 BC, showing Greek influence. One face depicts an owl and a combination of two letters; the other face shows a human face with a pammelsand nose on the cheek.'),('0- _10_p069_fbb166c8','currency','coin','unknown','human;owl','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',69,'Coin, metal. Ancient Yemeni coin showing Greek influence, with one face depicting an owl and a combination of two letters, and the other face depicting a human face with the nose shown on the cheek. Dated 354–340 BC. Weight 5.52 g.'),('0- _10_p070_89bc8721','jewelry','ring','gold','none','South Arabian antiquity','2nd century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',70,''),('0- _10_p071_9aa6662e','jewelry','ring','gold','none','South Arabian antiquity','5th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',71,'Earring, gold, with an open knot of the same material, semi-circular in shape, decorated with mannequin-shaped elements and a crater carved with adjacent lines. 5th century BC. 2.5 × 2.2 cm.'),('0- _10_p072_6288a421','currency','coin','unknown','human;owl','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',72,'Coin, metal, ancient Yemeni issue dated 354–340 BC, weighing 5.08 g. One face shows Greek influence, with an owl motif and a combination of two letters; the other side shows a human face, with a pammelsand nose on the cheek.'),('0- _10_p073_d8fc1a04','currency','coin','unknown','human;owl','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',73,'Coin, metal. Ancient Yemeni coin dated 354–340 BC, showing Greek influence. One face depicts an owl and a combination of two letters; the other face shows a human face with a pammelsand nose on the cheek.'),('0- _10_p074_c161f5cf','object','unknown','stone','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',74,'Star-shaped stone objects, two crystals of pyrotechnic stone, each mediated by a high-altitude bump with an iron ring for suspension. Islamic period, Qatar. Dimensions: 18 cm and 12 cm.'),('0- _10_p075_9f7ba027','currency','coin','silver','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',75,''),('0- _10_p076_234f216d','vessel','bowl','unknown','owl','Late Antiquity','14th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',76,'Vase, copper. Bowl with a wide nozzle and a condensed base, with the outer body decorated with a book-tape motif and vegetal ornament. Dated to the 14th–15th century, Qatar. Height 27 cm. Very good condition.'),('0- _10_p077_356687a5','object','unknown','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',77,''),('0- _10_p078_f2f3e7cb','currency','coin','silver','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',78,'Coin, metal, possibly silver, Islamic Yemeni currency with Arabic inscription in a surrounding written framework; the inscription reads “Sultan Muzaffar bin Yousif bin Al-Mama\'b.” Dated 650 H (1252 CE). Weight 1.82 g. Condition noted as good.'),('0- _10_p079_c497918f','currency','coin','silver','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',79,'Coin, metal, possibly silver, Islamic Yemeni currency with an Arabic inscription in a surrounding framework; the text includes “The God of Hila Muhammad ... [The Messenger of Hila].” Dated to the Apostolic period, 1249–1295, weight 1.91 g.'),('0- _10_p080_6756332a','jewelry','ring','wood','none','Late Antiquity','14th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',80,'Cylinder box, wood, cylindrical in shape, with cover, decorated with plant and geometric decorative elements executed in prominent carved relief. 14th century. Height 16.2 cm; diameter 20.3 cm. Very good condition.'),('0- _10_p081_235de0d7','currency','coin','silver','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_10.pdf',81,'Coin, metal, possibly silver, Muslim Yemeni, with an Arabic inscription