14.pdf',22,'Stone plate, marble, rectangular in form, with an inscribed line reading “Albister\'s pass.” Dated to the first century AD. Dimensions: 12 cm (4 3/4 in.); weight: 1.3 kg.'),('0- _14_p023_c2a532c9','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',23,''),('0- _14_p024_afae1a49','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',24,''),('0- _14_p025_c5010102','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',25,''),('0- _14_p026_2c507d36','object','unknown','marble','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',26,'Small object, marble, with two little horns projecting forward; length 7 cm (6 11/16 inches). First century BC. Excellent condition.'),('0- _14_p027_ec708607','sculpture','statue','marble','bull;horse','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',27,'Animal statues, marblestone. Four animal statues of different sizes and shapes, depicting a dog, a bull, and a horse, all standing on rectangular bases except the bull. First century BC. Largest 12 cm.'),('0- _14_p028_4041cb1f','jewelry','ring','gold','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',28,'Necklace, gold. Gold necklace with a decorative frame; described as comic and “gone” in the source text. Dated to 3000 BC. Weight 15 g, length 4 cm.'),('0- _14_p029_f769888f','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',29,'Human statue head, marble stone, carved in the round with a blindfolded treatment; likely from a statue. The head has two horizontal eyebrows with incised lines, a nose that is largely broken, a small visible horizontal upper lip, and a shallow horizontal line indicating the mouth opening. Ears are visible on both sides.'),('0- _14_p030_c5cb9878','sculpture','head','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','3rd century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',30,'Oyster, carved material, with the heads rendered very prominently and accurately, and the feet and chests carved small, visible, and light; dated to the 3rd century B.C. to 1st century A.D.'),('0- _14_p031_5ec6ec23','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',31,''),('0- _14_p032_82525ee5','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','3rd century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',32,'Human statue head, marble stone, carved with inlaid gemstone eyes; the eyebrows are rendered as two drifting horizontal lines, the nose is prominently carved, broad at the base, and the mouth is indicated by a horizontal line below. Marble stone. 3rd century B.C. / 1st century A.D.'),('0- _14_p033_f5cf6a94','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',33,''),('0- _14_p034_cb7f1f4c','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',34,''),('0- _14_p035_4c0a409e','sculpture','statue','unknown','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',35,'Statue, material not specified, depicting a human face with a prominent head, frontal features, button-like details, and a mouth carved in a small, visible, smiling manner; the front is marked by a blade-like line running from left to right with the letters L./Bester. Dated to the third to first century B.C.'),('0- _14_p036_90bc3926','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',36,'Object type not specified, material not specified. The source text identifies the item as “A witness’ grave” and includes the numbers “6 16 . 200 - 100 LOT - ART LOT - ART,” but provides no further factual description of the object, its material, typology, dimensions, technique, or date.'),('0- _14_p037_d8eb0074','object','unknown','bronze','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',37,'Scorpion, bronze. Bronze scorpion with six legs, three on each side, and a back appendage on the side. Dated to the 3rd–2nd century BC. Dimensions: 10 MS; 118.9 GG.'),('0- _14_p038_e61326bd','sculpture','statue','limestone','human','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',38,'Human statue head, limestone. Head of a human statue carved in limestone, with poorly carved eyes, two eyebrows rendered as a prominent arched form, a prominent nose, and a mouth represented by an empty horizontal line. Dated from the 3rd century BC to the 1st century AD.'),('0- _14_p039_ddf060e7','object','unknown','marble','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',39,'Stone plate, marble stone. The object is described as a stone plate with a weighted figure of Ruth Sahrb of the European Union; the left horn is broken, and the eyes are surrounded by high-profile lines. The text also identifies it as “Christmas ointment” and “LOT - ART Bad.”'),('0- _14_p040_58885c6e','object','unknown','limestone','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',40,'Limestone object, drawn from bottom to top, with a human face reflected on its surface.'),('0- _14_p041_6240297d','sculpture','statue','marble','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',41,'Statue, marble stone: oak statue on a rectangular base, with a prominent head hanging forward, two prominent eyes, and two curved horns extending to the back and beneath the ears.'),('0- _14_p042_78ff3cb5','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',42,'Object, material not specified. Dimensions recorded as 14 3/8 in. (36.3 cm). The source text is fragmentary and does not provide further descriptive, technical, or typological information.'),('0- _14_p043_1add3b82','inscribed object','tablet','bronze','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_14.pdf',43,'Rectangular tablet, bronze, with an engraved inscription in 12 lines. Metal: bronze. Dimensions: 23.5 × 15.7 cm. First century AD. The tablet has holes in the four corners and is described as in very good condition.'),('0- _1