'Candlestick, copper alloy, large candlestick of sect form, commissioned by a man of the legal tiles of Solomon, Turkey, Ottoman. Dated to the month of Al-Hajjay 945 AH / May 1539 CE. Height 47.5 cm.'),('0- _21_p003_6b5eae07','jewelry','ring','gold','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',3,''),('0- _21_p004_ab94b753','jewelry','ring','gold','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',4,''),('0- _21_p005_539ad6f3','jewelry','ring','marble','human','Late Antiquity','10th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',5,''),('0- _21_p006_84c0b921','object','unknown','limestone','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',6,''),('0- _21_p007_bba92ffb','sculpture','head','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',7,''),('0- _21_p008_4d2fd3f8','object','unknown','marble','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',8,''),('0- _21_p009_70022fb3','sculpture','statue','marble','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',9,''),('0- _21_p010_69ca4ac6','sculpture','statue','marble','goat','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',10,''),('0- _21_p011_de7c463c','sculpture','statue','marble','bull','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',11,''),('0- _21_p012_cb36e5e4','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',12,'Human statue, marble stone, small, standing on a thin rectangular base, with the hands extended forward and broken, and with empty eyes filled with cream stone. Dimensions: 13 3/8 × 4 3/4 × 4 5/16 in. (34 × 12 × 11 cm). Dated to the 2nd century BCE or 1st century CE.'),('0- _21_p013_5466316d','stone monument','tombstone','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',13,'Tombstone, marble, with a rectangular base and a single-line engraved inscription; polished marble stone. Dimensions: 5 7/8 x 3 15/16 x 3 5/16 in. (15 x 10 x 8.4 cm). Mid-2nd century.'),('0- _21_p014_587c3579','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',14,'Human statue head, marble stone, with a long neck encircled by three drifting lines; the face is partially preserved, with a broken nose and Lusitanian eyes. The head is associated with a limestone base bearing a two-line inscription and a two-line blade. Dimensions: 9 7/16 × 4 5/16 × 2 3/4 in. (24 × 11 × 7 cm).'),('0- _21_p015_8de652d6','jewelry','ring','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',15,'Mural, marble, 3rd century BCE. Fragmentary mural stone, broken straight across, preserving half of the composition with Thor’s head appearing in the middle. Inscribed with a single-line engraving reading “1-A-R-S.” Dimensions: 6 13/16 × 3 13/16 × 1 9/16 in. (17.3 × 9.7 × 4 cm).'),('0- _21_p016_7c432e20','inscribed object','plaque','marble','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',16,'Mural, marble stone, irregular plaque form, depicting a seated figure on a chair with the left hand raised and the right hand extended backward; beneath the figure is an inscription in a single line on the baseline reading “hj and t/t mr n.” Dimensions: 22.5 × 14.5 × 4 cm (8 7/8 × 5 11/16 × 1 9/16 in.). Dated to the second century BC.'),('0- _21_p017_19d0b722','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',17,''),('0- _21_p018_dfc398a6','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',18,''),('0- _21_p019_6a294d81','sculpture','statue','stone','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',19,''),('0- _21_p020_59f8ecef','sculpture','head','marble','bull','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',20,''),('0- _21_p021_a227a653','object','unknown','marble','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',21,''),('0- _21_p022_33194a38','object','unknown','marble','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',22,''),('0- _21_p023_0ecb35f6','object','unknown','stone','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',23,''),('0- _21_p024_dec4451a','object','unknown','stone','none','Late Antiquity','10th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',24,''),('0- _21_p025_de34ae55','jewelry','ring','bronze','none','Late Antiquity','3rd century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',25,''),('0- _21_p026_e8ab5e07','jewelry','ring','iron','human','Late Antiquity','5th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',26,'Necklace, iron, in the form of a human head wearing a turban, with a master maker above the necklace and a hole in the upper part. 1st to 5th century AD. Dimensions: 2 11/16 x 1 9/16 x 1 in. (6.8 x 4 x 2.5 cm).'),('0- _21_p027_ae3c4f62','object','unknown','stone','human','Late Antiquity','5th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',27,''),('0- _21_p028_5d8aee21','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',28,''),('0- _21_p029_d8585686','sculpture','statue','marble','human','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',29,''),('0- _21_p030_fbc5b747','sculpture','statue','marble','human','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',30,''),('0- _21_p031_bcd0f28f','sculpture','statue','unknown','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_21.pdf',31,'Human statue, material not specified, depicting a standing man in an upright pose with clear facial features; height 41.28 cm.'),('0- _22_p001_893a67b8','sculpture','statue','limestone','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',1,''),('0- _22_p002_bfc37e54','jewelry','ring','marble','none','Late Antiquity','1th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',2,''),('0- _22_p003_bb284de5','sculpture','statue','marble','bull','Late Antiquity','1th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',3,''),('0- _22_p004_4c5b844c','sculpture','statue','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',4,'Statue, marble, 12.1 x 19.1 cm, dated to 200–100 B.C.E. Rectangular marble statue of a woman with a clearly defined face; the front is broad at the eyes and narrows to a hard, pointed chin. The eyes are set beneath arched eyebrows and retain light-coloured residue; the nose is very long with a high bridge. The eyebrows are engraved, and a single line across the upper forehead appears to indicate a headband or similar head covering.'),('0- _22_p005_668e82c7','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',5,''),('0- _22_p006_b71734c4','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Islamic medieval','18th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',6,''),('0- _22_p007_0d42f868','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',7,''),('0- _22_p008_e6f7e902','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Islamic medieval','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',8,'Manuscript, paper, Hebrew and Arabic, Yemen, 19th century. The page describes three Yemeni manuscripts listed under this number at auction: a Hebrew manuscript with instructions and comments in the margins; a manuscript with Arabic instructions and a colophon on the last page; and a manuscript described as an Easter text with a Jewish translation into Arabic. All are on paper and dated to the 19th century.'),('0- _22_p009_ab2ed43b','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',9,'Hebrew manuscript on paper, dated 1848, comprising 227 leaves and written in two columns per page with red ink headings and dialects. The manuscript includes red and black decorative elements at the beginning of each Nir, except Nirs VI and VII, and a framed title page (blonin) bearing the inscription that the book was written in Sana\'a in 1848. Copies of the writer appear at the end of the book. It is described as a complete manuscript of formation, lacking a number of index leaves, and predating the well-known Livorno edition. Condition is noted as good.'),('0- _22_p010_7fb500f3','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',10,'Object, material not specified. The source text contains only fragmentary and repetitive bibliographic-style references, including the years 1895, 1894, 1934, 1986, and the notation “25 + 9 kedem [133],” but provides no identifiable object type, material, form, technique, dimensions, or period.'),('0- _22_p011_683adcce','jewelry','ring','unknown','none','Islamic medieval','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',11,'Manuscript, paper, Hebrew, 19th century. A bound manuscript containing a gathering of manuscripts and holy books from Yemen, including Third Megillot (Song of Songs, Ruth and Ecclesiastes) with commentary by Talmud, Rashi, and later combined commentaries such as Mahary Tsalakh, as well as Parashat Peshit’s papers with an adult explanation; the volume includes material at the beginning and end of the manuscript.'),('0- _22_p012_ec9c65d5','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Islamic medieval','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',12,'Hebrew manuscript on paper, two Yemeni manuscripts wrapped in the original skin, comprising liturgical and devotional texts. The first manuscript contains Piyyutim of Bakashot, Tikun Chatzot, interpretation of tekufot, shtarot, “Chiddushin,” Birkat Hamazon with Chiddushin, a eulogy, and a set of comments; it is dated 1864, includes different owner signatures, comprises 131 leaves, measures approximately 16.5 cm, and is in fair condition with bleeding, tears, and stains, with an old leather binding and popular decoration. The second manuscript contains piyyutim of Selichot and Hosha’anot, is dated to the 19th/20th century in Yemen, comprises approximately 168 leaves, measures about 16.5 cm, and is in good condition.'),('0- _22_p013_72b94c40','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',13,''),('0- _22_p014_f8a5f56a','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Islamic medieval','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',14,'Manuscript, paper; Hebrew manuscript for liturgical use throughout the year, including weekdays, Saturday, and festivals, in Yemeni writing in an animated letter, dated to the 19th century and measuring 17 cm. The manuscript contains a title page with the text “Seder of the hall according to the Safari tradition, written throughout the year...” and, on the back of the title page, “A copy of the lounge and the lounge according to our traditions in prayers throughout Yemeni cities.” It includes a weekly and Saturday service, Rosh Chodesh service, Birkat HaLevana, Seder Lashanah, Tekun Burim, Tekun Besash with Al-Hajdah, prayers for the three festivals, and the Zikhrot for Shaft. Some leaves were later replaced by another hand; several leaves are missing. The manuscript is in separate leaves, unbound, with spots, holes, tears affecting the text of several leaves, and engravings.'),('0- _22_p015_88c123d1','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',15,'Object, material not specified, with dimensions 19 x 11.5 cm. The record includes the number 200 and the term “kedem,” but no further descriptive information is provided.'),('0- _22_p016_cc4b6a73','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','19th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',16,'Hebrew manuscript on paper, 19th century, comprising 8 elements of differing size and condition. The elements vary in situation; some retain old ties, while others are newly associated. The manuscript is noted as being suitable for the equitable poor.'),('0- _22_p017_6abd9361','jewelry','ring','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',17,'Statue, marble. Statue of a standing male figure with both arms bent, the left hand clenched in a fist, wearing a short jacket. The face is straight-shaped with indicated eyebrows; the beard is rendered as a linear element extending from the ears down to the chin. The object is described as currently lost, with a missing patching.'),('0- _22_p018_439e9ea8','stone monument','tombstone','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',18,'Tombstone, marble. Carved funerary monument depicting a male bust in relief, with short hair at the back, a round face, heavy eyelids, a prominent nose, and a small mouth. Dated to around the 1st century B.C./A.D.'),('0- _22_p019_3b93fef1','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',19,'Object, material not specified. Recorded as “9.” with dimensions 14 (36.7), repeated in the source. Provenance or sale reference includes Bonhams, London, 26 2007, lot 223, with the date 2004 also noted in the source.'),('0- _22_p020_d68dbfc2','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',20,'Object type and material cannot be determined from the provided text. The source consists only of bibliographic references: “0.13 (34) Bonhams: 1972. pson 2002. 86. 88.” repeated twice, with no descriptive information about form, material, technique, dimensions, or date of the object itself.'),('0- _22_p021_05077278','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',21,'Object type not specified, with no descriptive information provided beyond the inventory/reference number 2002.196.274.'),('0- _22_p022_e2eb1dc8','sculpture','statue','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',22,'Statue, material not specified, depicting a woman standing on a rectangular base, with a pointed face, a prominent nose bridge extending to the eyebrows, and a bunch of facial features rendered in an obvious, stylized manner; dated to the first century BC; height 31 inches (79 cm).'),('0- _22_p023_23c77c9b','stone monument','tombstone','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',23,'Tombstone, marble. Carved tombstone depicting a woman’s grave with a long neck, an oval face with clearly defined facial features, including eyebrows carved above the eyes, a white-stone inlay, a long straight nose, and a small mouth.'),('0- _22_p024_df087257','object','unknown','wood','none','Late Antiquity','14th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',24,'Wooden object, wood, consisting of two bent wooden plaques, rectangular in shape, carved with inscriptions; one plaque bears a significant inscription in the third line beneath a strip of high hemispheres, and one is described as bearing a testimony. 14th century. Dimensions: 56 x 24 cm. Condition: good.'),('0- _22_p025_08380c5d','jewelry','ring','limestone','none','Late Antiquity','1st century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',25,''),('0- _22_p026_13970e3d','jewelry','ring','limestone','none','Late Antiquity','1st century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',26,''),('0- _22_p027_759f710f','sculpture','statue','unknown','bull','Late Antiquity','3rd century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',27,''),('0- _22_p028_66b11011','object','unknown','marble','none','Islamic medieval','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',28,''),('0- _22_p029_ff538274','jewelry','necklace','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',29,''),('0- _22_p030_cb31daf3','sculpture','bust','marble','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',30,'Bust, marble. Third century–first century BC. Height 7 1/4 inches (18.4 cm). Good condition.'),('0- _22_p031_22acfcad','jewelry','ring','stone','none','Late Antiquity','5th century','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_22.pdf',31,''),('0- _23_p001_3b177a57','sculpture','statue','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_23.pdf',1,''),('0- _23_p002_1bd278fb','jewelry','ring','marble','none','South Arabian antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_23.pdf',2,''),('0- _23_p003_a6f1b4cd','stone monument','tombstone','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_23.pdf',3,''),('0- _23_p004_09a953a0','stone monument','tombstone','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','0-آثارنا المنهوبة_23.pdf',4,'')