'object','unknown','stone','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',39,''),('29- _29_p040_6bce3745','sculpture','statue','marble','human','unknown','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',40,''),('29- _29_p041_5fbfa716','object','unknown','stone','none','Late Antiquity','6th century','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',41,''),('29- _29_p042_7a61ad2e','stone monument','tombstone','marble','none','Late Antiquity','1st century','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',42,''),('29- _29_p043_255b10d7','sculpture','statue','marble','bull;human','Late Antiquity','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',43,'Human statue, marble. Human statue in marble, dated to the first century BC. Height 20.9 cm. Condition: good.'),('29- _29_p044_2353c262','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',44,''),('29- _29_p045_5d5be489','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',45,''),('29- _29_p046_e7fde96b','object','unknown','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',46,''),('29- _29_p047_4ab8cf85','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','3rd century','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',47,''),('29- _29_p048_fee3ccb4','sculpture','statue','bronze','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','29-آثارنا المنهوبة_29.pdf',48,''),('31- _31_p002_86aafcec','sculpture','statue','limestone','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',2,'Human statue, limestone, depicting two interconnected human figures in a similar salt-like material. The figures have prominent eyes and noses, heads joined by a small cylindrical bridge, and short hands held against the chest.'),('31- _31_p003_29c5ae2a','sculpture','statue','stone','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',3,'Human statue, sandstone, a woman’s bust with a visible head, large eyes inlaid with gypsum and cream stones, high eyebrows with stone inserts, a high sharp nose, full lips, hair arranged in lines and falling behind the neck, and two distinct ears.'),('31- _31_p004_c8d52ea6','sculpture','statue','marble','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',4,'Statue, marble, human figure represented as a woman’s bust with jealous eyes retaining traces of black fixing material, a straight nose, a small mouth, and curly hair falling behind the shoulders.'),('31- _31_p005_2d74b8be','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',5,''),('31- _31_p006_56cb6e06','sculpture','statue','unknown','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',6,'Human statue, material not specified. A human statue described in the source as “A human statue.”'),('31- _31_p007_518f511e','jewelry','ring','bronze','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',7,'Human statue, bronze, depicting a standing woman with a pronounced pregnant abdomen. The head is upright, with a gang and a clearly defined ellipse wrapped backwards and hanging behind the shoulders. The arms are extended outward and the hands are open. The garment covers the body to mid-thigh. The legs are clearly modelled, with distinct toes. Height: 13.2 cm. Date: toward the 2nd century BC.'),('31- _31_p008_d07d17df','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',8,'Human statue, bronze, small flat-shaped figure representing a man in an abstract manner, standing in a long dress with both arms extended forward and holding a stick in the right hand; the figure is connected below to a small stabilization base. First millennium BC. Height: 13.7 cm.'),('31- _31_p009_5d598bbd','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',9,'Statuettes, bronze, four votive figurines representing human figures in an abstract manner, with unclear features; three are standing with outstretched, separate arms, and one is seated with the head missing; all are covered with a green layer of bronze corrosion. First millennium BC. Height: 2.2 to 4.2 cm.'),('31- _31_p010_26086da7','jewelry','ring','bronze','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',10,'Human statue fragment, bronze, preserving part of a hollow bronze figure: the left torso and shoulder, with a shield and a belt crossing the shoulders and extending to the back. First and second century C.E. Height: 21 cm.'),('31- _31_p011_4c06705e','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',11,'Statue, bronze: human statue preserving the bronze palm of the right hand, rendered at natural size with long fingers and covered with a green layer of bronze corrosion. Length: 13 cm.'),('31- _31_p012_36e90747','sculpture','statue','unknown','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',12,'Statue, material not specified. Human statue depicting a woman, with a clearly rendered head and well-executed features. The eyes are oval, the eyebrows are arched and raised, the nose is prominent and sharp with a rounded end, and the mouth is represented by a curved line.'),('31- _31_p013_2f2416a9','sculpture','statue','marble','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',13,'Statue head, marble, human figure, carved in stone. The object is described as the head of a statue, with a human form, made of marble.'),('31- _31_p014_e0f6de98','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',14,''),('31- _31_p015_c0b28629','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',15,''),('31- _31_p016_f4871bc9','sculpture','statue','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',16,'Human statue, marble. Statue of a man carved in white marble, with a clearly shaped and sharply cut head. The face is described as gloomy, with semi-oval carved eyes, eyebrows above the eyes, a pierced nose, full and relaxed lips, and ears clearly indicated on both sides of the head and pierced. The hairstyle consists of short locks arranged in square and rectangular forms, and the neck is broad.'),('31- _31_p017_aa106c3f','sculpture','statue','bronze','human','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',17,'Human statue, bronze. Head of a bronze statue representing a young man with a clear gaze; the eyes are prominent, the nose is straight, and the mouth has full lips. The hair is arranged in strands ending in forward and side waves, and the head is crowned with a vegetal wreath surmounted by a decorative element.'),('31- _31_p018_b1646d5e','sculpture','statue','marble','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',18,'Animal statue, marble, depicting a standing sheep with a clearly stylized form. The animal has large curved horns with spiral or snail-like terminals, a marked head, eyes not clearly represented, and a mouth indicated by a curved line. The body is cylindrical, and the statue stands on four legs. Dated to the second half of the 1st millennium BCE.'),('31- _31_p019_92190aac','sculpture','statue','bronze','male;deer','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',19,'Animal statue, bronze, depicting a young male deer in a crouching position with the body turned to the right. The head is defined, with prominent ears and short horns. The body is rendered in a fluid manner, and the front legs are missing. The surface is covered with a layer of green bronze corrosion. Dated to the second half of the first millennium BC.'),('31- _31_p020_7366c680','stone monument','tombstone','stone','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',20,''),('31- _31_p021_4561609d','stone monument','tombstone','limestone','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',21,'Tombstone, limestone. Rectangular grave marker with a human face in relief or carved depiction, showing raised eyebrows, rectangular nose, and a white mouth; described as “Jerry’s Stone.” Dated to the first century BCE.'),('31- _31_p022_02bfec92','stone monument','tombstone','limestone','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',22,'Tombstone, limestone. Irregular grave marker carved in limestone, with a sculpted human face. The source text describes it as an irregular, semi-rivaled grave of limestone and notes that the face was sculpted on a human face; no further details are provided.'),('31- _31_p023_42ffe533','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',23,'Object, material not specified, with dimensions 3.5 x 25.5.'),('31- _31_p024_3c4c4c31','stone monument','tombstone','limestone','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',24,''),('31- _31_p025_a27af77d','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',25,'Object type not specified, material not specified. The source text only gives the name “PERRE BERGE & Associes” and does not provide any archaeological or object-specific information.'),('31- _31_p026_d235d123','inscribed object','tablet','bronze','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',26,'Tablet, bronze, with an inscription and window holes distributed on three angles for stabilization. The engraved text records a vow made by a person named Saad El for the Abed, who was tried at Shebhan’s temple, invoking the gods Athtar, uncle, and prophet; the vow was made on his behalf and on behalf of his brother and his son. Dimensions recorded as 31.5 x 26.6 cm.'),('31- _31_p027_10b82af4','object','unknown','unknown','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',27,'Object type and material cannot be determined from the provided text, which appears to contain only a partial inscription or catalog notation with no descriptive information about the object itself.'),('31- _31_p028_dd1df250','jewelry','ring','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',28,'Rectangular plate of limestone, carved in low relief, depicting men wearing robes with carefully rendered folds; one figure is shown holding a saddle while another sits behind, both with head coverings framing a partial view of the face. The scene is arranged above a pin line and includes two lines of inscription. The source text also mentions marble and refers to the beginning of the Elephants of the Miles.'),('31- _31_p029_46c1dbc3','sculpture','head','marble','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',29,''),('31- _31_p030_267a9cea','object','unknown','limestone','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',30,'Painting, limestone. A painting made of limestone.'),('31- _31_p031_28432a4b','sculpture','head','bronze','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',31,'Plaque, bronze, rectangular plaque with a portrait composition in relief, showing three heads in frontal view, described as oak or bull heads, each with a prominent sculptural feature and a vegetal element above the head; the central head is framed by an engraved line and accompanied by an inscription of four characters reading “Bronze.”'),('31- _31_p032_371c7b9e','object','unknown','marble','none','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',32,'Marble, rectangular object with a square section, carved with two deep cavities on the upper surface with raised rims. One rectangular face bears a one-line rectangular inscription in the strand line, above which is a decorative frame of chain triangles; a distinct mass of stone remains on one side. The inscription reads: (WPB/LTN/RAAA/RAAN/W). Marble. Second half of the first millennium BC.'),('31- _31_p033_b5dd6f23','object','unknown','bronze','bull','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',33,'Architectural component, bronze: round disk mediated by an eight-pointed star enclosed in a circle, surrounded by a frame of twelve bulls with snail motifs. End of the first millennium BC. Diameter 15 cm.'),('31- _31_p034_3181947f','object','unknown','marble','human','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',34,''),('31- _31_p035_52be4054','glyptic','seal','gold','none','unknown','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',35,'Seal, gold. Circular seal with an empty-drilled vent; the face is mediated by an inscription in a rectangular frame, and from top to bottom a dam is carved in reverse motion position. The inscription reads: (m/pn/).'),('31- _31_p036_224b2bc3','jewelry','ring','gold','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',36,'Necklace, gold, formed as a spiraled wire with a central pendant representing the head of a hollow bull with short horns; on either side are two beads of planned faith, separated from the pendant by gold rings. Third century BC. Length: 5.15 cm.'),('31- _31_p037_20e4ce58','manuscript','manuscript','unknown','none','Late Antiquity','15th century','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',37,''),('31- _31_p038_c209f0d6','sculpture','head','limestone','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',38,''),('31- _31_p039_a2395d3d','sculpture','head','marble','bull','Late Antiquity','unknown','31-آثارنا المنهوبة_31.pdf',39,'Altar, marble. Cube-shaped altar flattened from the top of a bull’s head, with a clearly stylized form and carved inscription on the edge reading HBL/ML/SL/CTFR. Dated to the 5th–4th centuries BCE. Height: 28.2 cm; width: 8.2 cm.');
