cm and is covered with a South Arabian inscription.','Beaker, bronze, South Arabian, 4th–3rd century BCE. The vessel measures 13.1 cm in height and 7.5 cm in base diameter. It is covered with a South Arabian inscription. The object is described as being in very good condition. Provenance noted as ex Shlomo Moussaieff collection, Herzliyah.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-SOUTH-ARABIAN-BRONZE-BEAKER/594-south_arabian-13.10.22-archaeological','lot-art.com'),(61,'0- _10_p060_a08b7ee7','Inscription Translations: \"(1) Il-sharah of the clan Ma\'sum has dedicated (to) his god and his lord Hawkum Nabat and the gods (2) who are from Shim\'an, this bronze dedication (plaque), (just) as Hawkum had commanded by his oracle,  Private European Collection All items legal to buy/sell under U.S. LOT 64a South Arabian Leaded Bronze Votive Plaque ex-Christie\'s [ translate ] South Arabian, ca. And Il-sharah brought back the men of Hawkum, and sought (an oracular) response on his return (?) and (6) Hawkum made promise to Il-sha (7)rah by oracle, according as he (=Il-sharah) would offer to them (=the gods) the text and record. As a token of gratitude he dedicated this bronze plaque to the god Hawkum, one of the chief gods of Qataban. (See translation in extended description.) Leaded bronze has developed a beautiful green patina.\",1537',141,NULL,'','Plaque, leaded bronze, South Arabian. Bronze votive plaque with inscription dedicating the object to the god Hawkum, one of the chief gods of Qataban. The surface has developed a green patina.','Plaque, leaded bronze, South Arabian. Bronze votive plaque with inscription recording a dedication by Il-sharah of the clan Ma\'sum to his god and lord Hawkum Nabat and the gods from Shim\'an, made in accordance with an oracle. The text refers to the return of the men of Hawkum and to a promise made by Hawkum by oracle, and states that the plaque was offered as a token of gratitude. The object is described as a bronze dedication plaque and is noted as having developed a green patina.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/South-Arabian-Leaded-Bronze-Votive-Plaque-ex-Christies/64a-south_arabian-18.2.21-artemi','lot-art.com'),(62,'0- _10_p061_1748219e','LOT 677 A SOUTH ARABIAN BRONZE INCENSE BURNER DECORATED WITH PALM TREES FLANKED BY SPHINXES. [ translate ] A SOUTH ARABIAN BRONZE INCENSE BURNER DECORATED WITH PALM TREES FLANKED BY SPHINXES. With very nice brown patina and in very good condition (A small fragment is missing from the cover). The lid depicts floral motifs and all standing on 4 lion paws. Arabian incised and open worked inscription. Ex Shlomo Moussaieff collection, Herzliyah.',142,NULL,'','Incense burner, bronze, South Arabian, decorated with palm trees flanked by sphinxes. The vessel has a brown patina, a lid with floral motifs, an incised and openworked Arabian inscription, and stands on four lion paws; a small fragment is missing from the cover.','Incense burner, bronze, South Arabian, decorated with palm trees flanked by sphinxes. The object has a brown patina and is described as being in very good condition, with a small fragment missing from the cover. The lid is decorated with floral motifs, and the vessel stands on four lion paws. It bears an incised and openworked Arabian inscription. Provenance noted as ex Shlomo Moussaieff collection, Herzliyah.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-SOUTH-ARABIAN-BRONZE-INCENSE-BURNER-DECORATED-WITH-PALM-TREES-FLANKED-BY-SPHINXES/677-south_arabian-13.10.22-archaeological','lot-art.com'),(63,'0- _10_p062_e4da8aed','Hellenistic Period, 4th - 3rd century BCE. LOT 682 A SOUTH-ARABIAN BRONZE HORSE. [ translate ] A SOUTH-ARABIAN BRONZE HORSE. With nice green patina and in very good condition (Only remains of the original small wheels are preserved).',143,NULL,'','Horse, bronze, South Arabian, Hellenistic Period, 4th–3rd century BCE. Preserved with a green patina and in very good condition; only remains of the original small wheels survive.','Horse, 