d straight and stiff, with the hand in a semi-clenched fist. A triangular opening is present on both the chest and back, and a belt is wrapped around the waist, with short vertical grooves indicating clothing on the straight legs. The figure was likely mounted on an animal, possibly a camel, also modelled in bronze. The object measures 5 cm in height, excluding the stand. South Arabia is identified in the source as a region corresponding to parts of modern-day Yemen and extending into Oman, north to the Arabian oasis of Dedan, to Ethiopia, and as far as the East African coast into modern Tanzania.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/South-Arabian-Bronze-Statuette-of-a-Rider/64228291-south_arabian-05.12.22-catawiki','lot-art.com'),(65,'0- _10_p064_849e91cc','LOT 71 A SOUTH ARABIAN ALABASTER HEAD OF A WOMAN CIRCA 1ST CENTURY B.C. The Property of a Gentleman',145,NULL,'','Head, alabaster, South Arabian, circa 1st century B.C. Female head.','Head, alabaster, South Arabian, circa 1st century B.C. The object is a female head carved in alabaster. No further technical, dimensional, or contextual information is provided in the source text.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-SOUTH-ARABIAN-ALABASTER-HEAD-OF-/71-south_arabian-07.12.22-christie','lot-art.com'),(66,'0- _10_p065_20d411b4','LOT 152 A SOUTH ARABIAN ALABASTER FIGURE OF A STANDING MALE [ translate ] A SOUTH ARABIAN ALABASTER FIGURE OF A STANDING MALEcarved in one whole piece of alabaster, the standing figure wearing a tunic and raised on an integral base, carved with an inscription,42cm high Past » View it on Login » View it on Login Estimate Unlock Reserve Unlock Time, Location 20 Oct 2022 UK, London Auction House Unlock [ translate ] A SOUTH ARABIAN ALABASTER FIGURE OF A STANDING MALEcarved in one whole piece of alabaster, the standing figure wearing a tunic and raised on an integral base, carved with an inscription,42cm high Estimate Unlock Reserve Unlock Time, Location 20 Oct 2022 UK, London Auction House