Imitative-Owl-Drachm/3548-south_arabian-02.3.20-timeline','lot-art.com'),(74,'0- _10_p073_d8fc1a04','Obv: head of Athena right, wearing crested helmet and circular ear ring, eye in profile',154,NULL,'','Coin, metal, with obverse showing the head of Athena facing right, wearing a crested helmet and circular earring; the eye is shown in profile.','Coin, metal, with obverse depicting the head of Athena facing right. She wears a crested helmet and a circular earring, and the eye is rendered in profile. No further details are provided in the source text.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/South-Arabian-Sabaean-Imitative-Owl-Drachm/3545-south_arabian-02.3.20-timeline','lot-art.com'),(75,'0- _10_p074_c161f5cf','LOT 5 Yemen [ translate ] Yemen 2 oil lamps Stone carved in the shape of a star wrought iron grip ring D. 18 cm and 12 cm Automatically translated by DeepL. To see the original version, click here.',155,NULL,'','Oil lamp, stone, carved in the shape of a star, with wrought iron grip ring. Yemen.','Oil lamp, stone, carved in the shape of a star, with a wrought iron grip ring. The object is described as originating from Yemen. Dimensions given: 18 cm and 12 cm.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/Yemen/5-yemen-28.3.20-fauvepari','lot-art.com'),(76,'0- _10_p076_234f216d','LOT 48 A Rasulid brass basin Yemen, 14th/ 15th Century [ translate ] A Rasulid brass basin Yemen, 14th/ 15th Century of rounded form with tapering sides, the body decorated with an engraved band containing inscription-filled cartouches overlaid with rosettes interspersed by roundels containing flowerheads and foliate interlace, the interstices with lozenge motifs, the well with a rosette 27 cm.',157,NULL,'','Basin, brass, Yemen, 14th/15th century. Rounded form with tapering sides, decorated with an engraved band of inscription-filled cartouches overlaid with rosettes, roundels containing flowerheads and foliate interlace, and lozenge motifs in the interstices; the well has a rosette. Diameter 27 cm.','Basin, brass, Yemen, 14th/15th century. The vessel is of rounded form with tapering sides and is decorated on the body with an engraved band containing inscription-filled cartouches overlaid with rosettes. These are interspersed by roundels containing flowerheads and foliate interlace, while the interstices are filled with lozenge motifs. The well is decorated with a rosette. The basin measures 27 cm in diameter.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-Rasulid-brass-basin-Yemen-14th-15th-Century/48-rasulid_bra-26.5.22-bonham','lot-art.com'),(77,'0- _10_p078_f2f3e7cb','LOT 0722A006D995 SOLD. [ translate ] Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid-Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, 1249–1295, Dirhem, \'Adan, AH 650 (1252 AD), 1.82 g. Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid-Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, 1249-1295, Dirhem, \'Adan, AH 650 (1252 AD), 1.82 g....',159,NULL,'','Dirhem, silver, Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, struck at \'Adan, AH 650 (1252 AD), 1.82 g.','Dirhem, silver, Islamic coin from Yemen, issued under the Rasulid Dynasty during the reign of al-Muzaffar Yusuf (1249–1295). The coin was struck at \'Adan and dated AH 650 (1252 AD). Recorded weight: 1.82 g.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/SOLD-Islamic-Yemen-Rasulid-Dynasty-al-Muzaffar-Yusuf-1249-1295-Dirhem-Adan-AH-650-1252-AD-182-g/722a006d995-sold_islamic-27.9.20-bruun','lot-art.com'),(78,'0- _10_p079_c497918f','LOT 858CD4CB5452 SOLD. [ translate ] Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid-Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, 1249–1295, Dirhem, mint Adan, 1.91 g. Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid-Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, 1249-1295, Dirhem, mint Adan.',160,NULL,'','Dirhem, silver, Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid Dynasty, al-Muzaffar Yusuf, 1249–1295, mint of Adan, 1.91 g.','Dirhem, silver, Islamic, Yemen, Rasulid Dynasty, issued under al-Muzaffar Yusuf (1249–1295), minted at Adan, weighing 1.91 g. The object is identified as an Islamic dirhem from Yemen and the source text provides the ruler, dynasty, mint, and weight.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/SOLD-Islamic-Yemen-Rasulid-Dynasty-al-Muzaffar-Yusuf-1249-1295-Dirhem-mint-Adan-Bruun-Rasmussen-Auctioneers-of/858cd4cb5452-sold_islamic-25.10.20-bruun','lot-art.com'),(79,'0- _10_p080_6756332a','LOT 0164 A RASULID LACQUERED CYLINDIRCAL WOOD BOX, EGYPT OR YEMEN, 14TH CENTURY [ translate ] With flat base and slightly sloping sides, the upper edge with slight recess to fit a lid, the exterior wooden surface overlaid in a succession of black, red, yellow and green lacquers, then carved through to reveal a polychrome design, the broad central band with lobed rectangular panels containing scrolling arabesques around quatrefoil roundels, the borders of the panels entwining and continuing into lobed concentric quatrefoils dividing each panel, a band below of stylized thuluth calligraphy interrupted by roundels containing quatrefoil panels, the base and interior plain with remains of monochrome lacquer, 16.2 cm. The technique of decoration of our box is in the same tradition ans would point to an attribution to 14th or 15th century Mamluk Egypt indicated by the finds from Qusair al-Qadim.â€¨â€¨The shape of our object has counterparts in other items from Mamluk Egypt. diam.PROVENANCE Christieâ€™s, 17th October 1995, lot 269.Private collection, GreeceCATALOGUE NOTE While later Islamic lacquer has been studied extensively, the history of the technique in early Islamic times is still obscure. Given the possible Chinese origins of the technique it is certainly relevant that there exist a number of 15th century cylindrical lidded boxes from China, decorated in a Chinese manner with peony scrolls and phoenixes (Garner, Sir H.: Chinese lacquer, London, 1979, figs. In Persia a small fragment was found during the excavations at Ghubayra which has been given a thirteenth century attribution (Fehervari, G., â€˜Near Eastern Lacquerwork',161,NULL,'','Box, wood, cylindrical, with flat base and slightly sloping sides, 14th century, Egypt or Yemen. The exterior is overlaid with black, red, yellow, and green lacquers and carved through to form a polychrome decorative design with scrolling arabesques, quatrefoil roundels, lobed rectangular panels, and stylized thuluth calligraphy.','Box, wood, cylindrical, with flat base and slightly sloping sides and a slight recess at the upper edge to receive a lid, 14th century, Egypt or Yemen. The exterior wooden surface is overlaid in successive layers of black, red, yellow, and green lacquer and carved through to reveal a polychrome decoration. The broad central band is composed of lobed rectangular panels containing scrolling arabesques around quatrefoil roundels, with panel borders that entwine and continue into lobed concentric quatrefoils dividing each panel. Below is a band of stylized thuluth calligraphy interrupted by roundels containing quatrefoil panels. The base and interior are plain, with remains of monochrome lacquer. The object measures 16.2 cm in diameter.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/A-RASULID-LACQUERED-CYLINDIRCAL-WOOD-BOX-EGYPT-OR-YEMEN-14TH-CENTURY/164-rasulid_lacquered-24.5.22-orientartauc','lot-art.com'),(80,'0- _10_p081_235de0d7','(A.1105), lightly toned, obverse good very fine, reverse a crude cut die, but very fine, extremely rare *ex Spink Zurich Auction 31, 20th June 1989, Lot 178. LOT 3093 Islamic Coins [ translate ] Rasulid, al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696-721h), silver dirham, Dufar, 721h, wt. Dufar was the easternmost Rasulid mint established in the old port town, today it is now the centre of the modern Omani city of Salalah.',162,NULL,'','Coin, silver dirham. Rasulid, al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696-721h), struck at Dufar in 721h. Lightly toned, with obverse in good very fine condition and reverse from a crude cut die, but very fine.','Coin, silver dirham. Rasulid issue of al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696-721h), struck at Dufar in 721h. The coin is lightly toned; the obverse is described as good very fine, while the reverse is from a crude cut die but remains very fine. Dufar was the easternmost Rasulid mint, established in the old port town that is now the centre of the modern Omani city of Salalah. The piece is noted as extremely rare.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/Islamic-Coins/3093-islamic_coin-26.10.21-baldwin','lot-art.com'),(81,'0- _10_p082_6e058211','RASULID (Yemen), Al-Mudhaffar Samsaddin Yusuf (AH in Switzerland LOT 4010 RASULID (Yemen), Al-Mudhaffar Samsaddin Yusuf (AH [ translate ] Album 1102. XF 4495 Past » View it on Login Sale price Unlock Estimate Unlock Time, Location 08 Nov 2017 Switzerland, Lausanne Auction House Unlock [ translate ] Album 1102. XF 4495 Sale price Unlock Estimate Unlock Time, Location 08 Nov 2017 Switzerland, Lausanne Auction House Unlock Past » View it on Login',163,NULL,'','Coin, metal, attributed to the Rasulid period (Yemen), under Al-Mudhaffar Samsaddin Yusuf. Album 1102, XF 4495.','Coin, metal, attributed to the Rasulid period in Yemen, under Al-Mudhaffar Samsaddin Yusuf. The source text identifies it as Album 1102, XF 4495. No further technical, typological, dimensional, or chronological details are provided in the source.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lots/RASULID-Yemen-Al-Mudhaffar-Samsaddin-Yusuf-AH/4010-rasulid_yemen-08.11.17-numismatique','lot-art.com'),(82,'0- _10_p083_ac6e1897','LOT 3020 Islamic Coins [ translate ] Islamic Coins, Rasulid, al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696-721h), gold dinar, ‘Adan 718h, wt. The principle difference is that, unlike the latter, the Rasulids included both the mint name and date in their legends. These gold issues may have been issued to facilitate trade with India.',164,NULL,'','Coin, gold. Rasulid gold dinar of al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696–721 AH), struck at ‘Adan in 718 AH.','Coin, gold. Rasulid gold dinar of al-Mu’ayyad Da’ud (696–721 AH), struck at ‘Adan in 718 AH. The source notes that, unlike the latter, the Rasulids included both the mint name and date in their legends. These gold issues may have been issued to facilitate trade with India.','https://www.lot-art.com/auction-lot