South Arabian inscription consisting of three letters. The object is described as a large oil lamp; no further technical details, dimensions, or chronology are provided in the source text.','https://www.pba-auctions.com/lot/7974/1617595?refurl=Grande+lampe+%C3%A0+huile+dont+les+bords+sont+orn%C3%A9s+de+rinceaux+de+lierre+et+l%27arri%C3%A8re+d%27une+inscription+','pba-auctions.com'),(102,'0- _5_p007_712e95bc','H_45,5 cm L_18,2 cm South Arabian limestone stelae. Informations sur la vente - Archéologie Archéologie Expositions publiques: Drouot-Richelieu - Salle 1 Mercredi 30 et Jeudi 31 Mai de 11 heures à 18 heures Vendredi 1er Juin de 11 heures à 12 heures Téléphone pendant l\'exposition publique: +33 (0)1 48 00 20 01 Experts: Christophe Kunicki T. Lot n° 185 Aller au lot Estimation : 3000 - 4000 EUR Résultats sans frais Résultat : 7 000EUR Stèle iconique. +33 (0)1 43 25 84 34 c.kunicki@orange.fr Conditions de vente - Archéologie CLIQUEZ ICI POUR TÉLÉCHARGER LES CONDITIONS DE VENTES Mes ordres d\'achat Informations sur la vente Conditions de vente Retourner au catalogue Stèle rectangulaire sculptée au sommet d\'un - Lot 185 Stèle iconique. Elle est gravée d\'une inscription de trois lettres sudarabiques: nom du propriétaire. Stèle rectangulaire sculptée au sommet d\'un visage triangulaire stylisé. Péninsule sudarabique, fin du Ier millénaire av.',265,NULL,'','Stela, South Arabian limestone, H. 45.5 cm, L. 18.2 cm. Rectangular stela with a stylised triangular face at the top and an inscription of three South Arabian letters identifying the owner. South Arabian Peninsula, late 1st millennium BC.','Stela, South Arabian limestone, H. 45.5 cm, L. 18.2 cm. Rectangular stela carved with a stylised triangular face at the top. It is engraved with an inscription in three South Arabian letters, identified in the source as the name of the owner. The object is described as an iconic stela and is attributed to the South Arabian Peninsula, late 1st millennium BC.','https://www.pba-auctions.com/lot/12242/2420201?npp=20&','pba-auctions.com'),(103,'0- _5_p008_3ad06fef','H_38,2 cm L_21,2 cm South Arabian alabaster stelae. Sale information - Archéologie Archéologie Expositions publiques: Drouot-Richelieu - Salle 1 Mercredi 30 et Jeudi 31 Mai de 11 heures à 18 heures Vendredi 1er Juin de 11 heures à 12 heures Téléphone pendant l\'exposition publique: +33 (0)1 48 00 20 01 Experts: Christophe Kunicki T. Lot n° 184 Go to lot Estimation : 7000 - 9000 EUR Result without fees Result : 23 000EUR Stèle iconique. +33 (0)1 43 25 84 34 c.kunicki@orange.fr Sales conditions - Archéologie CLIQUEZ ICI POUR TÉLÉCHARGER LES CONDITIONS DE VENTES My orders Sale information Sales conditions Return to catalogue Stèle rectangulaire sculptée au sommet d\'un - Lot 184 Stèle iconique. Bibliographie comparative: Yémen, au pays de la reine de Saba, catalogue d\'exposition, Paris, 1997, p. Le long nez fin et triangulaire est flanqué d\'yeux gravés, la pupille indiquée. Stèle rectangulaire sculptée au sommet d\'un visage de face stylisé.',266,NULL,'','Stela, alabaster. South Arabian rectangular icon stela with a stylised frontal face carved at the top. The face has a long, thin, triangular nose flanked by engraved eyes with indicated pupils.','Stela, alabaster. South Arabian rectangular icon stela, sculpted at the top with a stylised frontal face. The facial features are rendered in a simplified manner, with a long, thin, triangular nose flanked by engraved eyes and indicated pupils. The object is described as a rectangular stela carved at the summit with a stylised face seen from the front. Comparative bibliography cited in the source: Yémen, au pays de la reine de Saba, exhibition catalogue, Paris, 1997.','https://www.pba-auctions.com/en/lot/12242/2420200?','pba-auctions.com'),(104,'0- _5_p009_e7a20612','Arts of the Islamic World including Fine Rugs and Carpets / Lot 194 194 A SILVER SWORD (SAIF) AND SCABBARD, YEMEN, 19TH CENTURY | Estimate 4,000 - 6,000 GBP bidding is closed Description 80cm. the single-edged triple fullered curved steel blade set with a silver-plated hilt with engraved decoration, the silver-plated scabbard with engraved vegetal motifs Condition Overall in good condition, minor patination to the blade, minor oxidation, minor dents and the knucle chain missing, as viewed. \"In response to your inquiry, we are pleased to provide you with a general report of the condition of the property described above. Since we are not professional conservators or restorers, we urge you to consult with a restorer or conservator of your choice who will be better able to provide a detailed, professional report. Prospective buyers should inspect each lot to satisfy themselves as to condition and must understand that any statement made by Sotheby\'s is merely a subjective, qualified opinion. Prospective buyers should also refer to any Important Notices regarding this sale, which are printed in the Sale Catalogue. NOTWITHSTANDING THIS REPORT OR ANY DISCUSSIONS CONCERNING A LOT, ALL LOTS ARE OFFERED AND SOLD AS IS\" IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE CONDITIONS OF BUSINESS PRINTED IN THE SALE CATALOGUE.\" Catalogue Note Swords of this type were used in Yemen and Oman in the nineteenth century. The decoration of the hilt, with intricate floral scrolls, is reminiscent of similar workmanship produced in Hyderabad, a testimony of the strong links between India and the Arabian peninsula. For three comparable examples, see Hales 2013, p.245.',267,NULL,'','Sword (saif) and scabbard, silver-plated steel and silver-plated metal, Yemen, 19th century. Single-edged triple-fullered curved steel blade with a silver-plated hilt and engraved decoration, accompanied by a silver-plated scabbard with engraved vegetal motifs.','Sword (saif) and scabbard, silver-plated steel and silver-plated metal, Yemen, 19th century. The sword measures 80 cm and has a single-edged, triple-fullered curved steel blade set with a silver-plated hilt decorated with engraved floral scrolls. The silver-plated scabbard is decorated with engraved vegetal motifs. The object is described as being in overall good condition, with minor patination to the blade, minor oxidation, minor dents, and the knuckle chain missing.','https://www.sothebys.com/en/auctions/ecatalogue/2019/arts-of-the-islamic-world-l19220/lot.194.html','sothebys.com'),(105,'0- _5_p009_16162ad0','Brazier of Rasulid Sultan al-Malik al-Muzaffar Shams al-Din Yusuf ibn \'Umar second half 13th century On view at The Met Fifth Avenue in Gallery 454 Braziers served as portable grills and heaters. The lionheaded knobs with rings provided receptacles for handles to transport the heated unit, while the confronted dragon heads on each side functioned as spit brackets. The names and honorifics mentioned in the monumental inscription identify the patron, the second ruler of the Rasulid dynasty (r. 1250–95). His dynastic emblem, a five‑petalled rosette upon a circular shield, features prominently on both sides of each corner bracket. Artwork Details Object Information Overview Catalogue Entry Signatures, Inscriptions, and Markings Provenance Exhibition History References Title: Brazier of Rasulid Sultan al-Malik al-Muzaffar Shams al-Din Yusuf ibn \'Umar Date: second half 13th century Geography: Probably made in Egypt Medium: Brass',268,NULL,'','Brazier, brass, second half 13th century. Probably made in Egypt. The object is associated with Rasulid Sultan al-Malik al-Muzaffar Shams al-Din Yusuf ibn \'Umar and bears a monumental inscription naming the patron.','Brazier, brass, second half 13th century. Probably made in Egypt. This portable brazier was used as a grill and heater. It has lion-headed knobs with rings that served as receptacles for handles to transport the heated unit, and confronted dragon heads on each side that functioned as spit brackets. The monumental inscription names and honors the patron, identified as the second ruler of the Rasulid dynasty, al-Malik al-Muzaffar Shams al-Din Yusuf ibn \'Umar (r. 1250–95). His dynastic emblem, a five-petalled rosette on a circular shield, appears prominently on both sides of each corner bracket.','https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/444540','metmuseum.org'),(106,'31- _31_p002_86aafcec','Because of their age and their nature, many lots are not in their original condition and some descriptions in the catalogue or in the condition report may, in some cases, mention damages and / or restoration References in the catalogue description, or in the condition report, on an accident or a restoration are made to facilitate the inspection by potential bidders and are subject to the assessment that must be the result of a personal examination by the buyer or his appropriate representative. AVIS IMPORTANT: Pour les lots dont le vendeur est non - résident, l’adjudicataire paiera une TVA de 5,5% en sus de l’adjudication (lots signalés par) (le montant de cette TVA sera remboursé sur présentation de la preuve d’exportation hors CEE, dans un délai maximum d’un mois). 169 Informations sur la vente - ARCHÉOLOGIE Expositions publiques Jeudi 27 novembre de 11 heures à 18 heures Vendredi 28 novembre de 11 heures à 18 heures Samedi 29 novembre de 11 heures à 12 heures Thursday November 27th from 11:00 am to 6:00 pm Friday November 28th from 11:00 am to 6:00 pm Saturday November 29th from 11:00 am to 12:00 am Téléphone pendant l’exposition publique T. Should Pierre Bergé & associés recognise two simultaneous bids on an object, the lot will be put up for sale again and all those present in the saleroom may participate in thissecond opportunity to bid. Lot n° 169 Aller au lot Estimation : 3000 - 3500 EUR Résultats sans frais Résultat : 5 800EUR DOUBLE STATUETTE. Les informations relatives aux dimensions d’un lot figurant dans la description du catalogue ou dans le rapport d’état sont communiquées à titre indicatif et ne sont pas garanties. Du fait de leur ancienneté et de leur nature, de nombreux lots ne sont pas dans leur état d’o