5th century Figure of the Virgin Estimate: 5,000 - 7,000 USD Bolognese School, early 17th century Portrait of a boy, bust-length, in a white ruff Estimate: 8,000 - 12,000 GBP Charles Théodore Frère Encampment in the desert Estimate: 40,000 - 60,000 GBP Charles James Theriat The Caravan Estimate: 30,000 - 50,000 GBP Nasreddine (Etienne) Dinet A Captive Audience Estimate: 50,000 - 70,000 GBP Lot Details Description A South Arabian Alabaster Figure of a Woman, Qataban 3rd Century B.C./1st Century A.D. Rautenburghs Trompe l\'œil with letters Estimate: 6,000 - 8,000 GBP Italian, Sienese, 15th century Figure of the Virgin Estimate: 5,000 - 7,000 USD Bolognese School, early 17th century Portrait of a boy, bust-length, in a white ruff Estimate: 8,000 - 12,000 GBP Charles Théodore Frère Encampment in the desert Estimate: 40,000 - 60,000 GBP Charles James Theriat The Caravan Estimate: 30,000 - 50,000 GBP Nasreddine (Etienne) Dinet A Captive Audience Estimate: 50,000 - 70,000 GBP Originally from the storied collection of Christiane and Antonin Besse who lovingly built a collection of South Arabian sculpture while living in the then British colony of Aden in the middle 20 th century (see ), this sculpture stands as a compelling testament to the religious life, social structure, and artistic sophistication of ancient South Arabia, offering rare insight into a culture whose visual traditions remain less familiar than those of its contemporaries, yet equally rich and expressive. This lot has been withdrawn Lot Details Description A South Arabian Alabaster Figure of a Woman, Qataban 3rd Century B.C./1st Century A.D. Origins II Origins II A South Arabian Alabaster Figure of a Woman, Qataban, 3rd Century B.C./1st Century A.D. Carved from translucent calcite-alabaster, a material prized for its luminous qualities, the figure displays the stylized aesthetic characteristic of South Arabian figurative art: a frontal pose, simplified bodily forms, and an emphasis on facial presence and symmetry. Originally, such figures may have featured painted details or inlaid facial detailing, such as extant here in the figures recessed eyes, enhancing their lifelike presence and ritual impact. You May Also Like Charles Robertson The Wailing Wall Estimate: 100,000 - 150,000 GBP Stanislaus von Chlebowski A Dervish before the Mosque Estimate: 80,000 - 120,000 GBP Fabio Fabbi Portrait of Markos Botsaris, after Jean-Léon Gérôme Estimate: 60,000 - 80,000 GBP Alberto Pasini Caravan traversing a mountain pass Estimate: 80,000 - 120,000 GBP C.',355,NULL,'','Figure of a woman, alabaster, Qataban, 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D. South Arabian sculpture carved from translucent calcite-alabaster, with a frontal pose, simplified bodily forms, and recessed eyes.','Figure of a woman, alabaster, Qataban, 3rd century B.C./1st century A.D. South Arabian sculpture carved from translucent calcite-alabaster. The figure is described as displaying the stylized aesthetic characteristic of South Arabian figurative art, with a frontal pose, simplified bodily forms, and an emphasis on facial presence and symmetry. The recessed eyes are noted as extant, and the text states that such figures may originally have featured painted details or inlaid facial detailing. The object is identified as a South Arabian alabaster figure of a woman from Qataban.','https://www.sothebys.com/en/buy/auction/2026/origins-sa2601/a-south-arabian-alabaster-figure-of-a-woman','sothebys.com'),(109,'31- _31_p006_56cb6e06','Because of their age and their nature, many lots are not in their original condition and some descriptions in the catalogue or in the condition report may, in some cases, mention damages and / or restoration References in the catalogue description, or in the condition report, on an accident or a restoration are made to facilitate the inspection by potential bidders and are subject to the assessment that must be the result of a personal examination by the buyer or his appropriate representative. 